title: Grateful Dead Live at Carter-Finley Stadium on 1990-07-10
description:
Set 1

Jack Straw*, Loser, We Can Run But We Can't Hide, Me & My Uncle-> Big River, Friend Of The Devil*, When I Paint My Masterpiece*, Bird Song*, Promised Land**

Set 2

Iko Iko*, Playin' In The Band*-> Uncle John's Band*-> Playin' In The Band Jam-> Drums-> Jam-> The Other One-> Stella Blue, Not Fade Away, E: Brokedown Palace

* with Bruce Hornsby on accordion. ** Done in 2 parts, power goes out; Bruce Hornsby & the Range opened

files.title: Mr. Currier's Master GD Metal Tapes

reviews.review_text: - Pretty good sound, though a little pokey at first, it gets better. First set patchy but basically great. Audience noise a bit annoying...and what are they booing about? Deadheads go home! Anyway, 2nd set tremendous with drums/space unusually noteworthy.

The boos The crowd was booing the cops.  At the time Carter Finley Stadium just had a grass hill behind the South(?) end zone.  Heads were sliding down the hill to the bottom.  Of course the cops felt they had to get involved and put an end to it.  A couple of them busted their ass in the process.  It was really entertaining!
Carter/Finley This was an awesome show until the cops played nasty,But when Hornsby took the stage with his accordian,it was almost worth it.
